in this course we want to learn how to design
"reusable" & "extensible" object oriented software.

Design Patterns are "Elegant solutions" to repeating problems.
like we want to implement undo mechanism,
that's the repeating problem in software design!
we have some pattern to implement it,
like "MEMENTO PATTERN"
these patterns shows you how to structure your classes
and how these classes should talk to each other.

in this course we will explore 23 design patterns!
they documented in th 90s in the book called:
design patterns (elements of reusable "object-oriented" software)
By GOF (Gang Of Four) (the book has 4 authors!)
so it's usual called these 23 patterns as
"GANG OF FOUR PATTERNS!"

gang of four patterns include 23 design patterns in three categories
1.Creational  (ways to creat objects)
2.Structural  (about the relations between these objects)
3.Behavioural (about interaction or communication between these objects)

Note: we will talk about the "behavioral" design pattern
      in part 1 of this course.
      INTERACTION OR COMMUNICATION BETWEEN OUR CLASSES
      like mediator, observer, memento, strategy,...

Note: understanding design pattern will help us to
      learn frameworks so quickly!
      they will be just syntax!

